{
  format: 1
  name: required-namespace-removed-fails-reopen
  suite: scenario
  spec: ["#host-namespaces", "#conformance", "#loading"]
  tags: ["availability", "supply-chain"]
  note: '''
    Attack: strip a running application's declared dependency from the host
    to force it to reactivate against an incomplete context — an
    availability/denial vector distinct from interface drift. The package is
    installed and live against test.util@1. The host context is then rebuilt
    with NO namespaces registered and the store reopened. §2.1: "a package
    requiring an unavailable or incompatible component fails validation
    before activation." §16.2: "Missing ... requirements reject loading
    before the package becomes active." §9.2: open "validates the recorded
    active composition and required definitions before making the
    application available. A diagnostic leaves the prior active composition
    unchanged." So open MUST produce a diagnostic and MUST NOT bring the
    application up in a state where util.double is unresolved; durable state
    is left intact. Extension step `reopen` is defined in NOTES.md; FORMAT.md
    outcome `invalid` maps to the open-time validation diagnostic.
    This differs from pinned-descriptor-drift-fails-reopen: there the
    namespace is present but incompatible; here it is absent (unavailable).
    (Recast per §16.5: the `util.double` carrier moved out of a
    database-evaluated `$view` into the mutation body — its one legal
    position — so the removal-at-reopen mechanic under test is
    position-independent; the mutation `add` exercises the live descriptor
    before it is stripped.)
  '''

  package: {
    $liasse: 1
    $app: "t.nsremoved@1.0.0"
    $requires: {
      util: "test.util@1"
    }
    $model: {
      nums: {
        $key: "id"
        id: "text"
        n: "int"
        doubled: "int = 0"
      }
      $mut: {
        add: [
          "d = util.double(@n)"
          "row = .nums + { id: @id, n: @n, doubled: d }"
          "return row { id, doubled }"
        ]
      }
      $public: {
        nums: { $view: ".nums { id, n, doubled }", $mut: { add: ".add" } }
      }
    }
  }

  hosts: {
    namespaces: [
      {
        id: "test.util"
        version: "1.2.0"
        interface_hash: "ih-util-1"
        functions: {
          double: { signature: "(int) -> int", effect: "pure", op: "double" }
        }
      }
    ]
  }

  steps: [
    // application is genuinely live before the dependency is stripped
    { call: "public.nums.add", args: { id: "r1", n: "7" },
      expect: { outcome: ok, value: { id: "r1", doubled: "14" } } }
    // reopen the durable store against a context missing the required namespace
    { reopen: { hosts: { namespaces: [] } }
      expect: {
        outcome: invalid
        violates: ["#host-namespaces", "#conformance"]
      } }
  ]
}
